      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OAKHAY (5) is a quality gelding who has put together two wins and six minor placings from eight starts this campaign. Kept the ball rolling last start when he finished third over 1800m at this track, beaten by 3.5 metres. Good enough to win a race of this calibre. CAPTAINS DREAM (3) was third at this track two runs back and again performed impressively at the most recent appearance, making up plenty of ground before the turn but finding one better over 1800m at this track. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. This looks a sterner test than last time but he is capable of adding to the fine recent form. SEA HUNTER (9) is in the mix following a respectable third at his most recent appearance over 1800m at this track. SKINNY HORACE (7) is worth plenty of thought off a last-start win by a nose at Port Pirie over 2050m.",
